0:{"buildId":"3_8tk2yXshjsX4BxM6gAi","rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"How to Write a Privacy Policy for Your SaaS App in 2026\",\"description\":\"Step-by-step guide to writing a privacy policy for SaaS applications. Covers GDPR, CCPA, data collection disclosures, third-party services, and a practical SaaS privacy policy template.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-03-16\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-03-16\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Codepliant\",\"url\":\"https://codepliant.dev\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Codepliant\",\"url\":\"https://codepliant.dev\"},\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://codepliant.dev/blog/privacy-policy-for-saas\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"py-20 px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[680px] mx-auto","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-accent mb-4 tracking-wide uppercase","children":"Blog"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4","children":"How to Write a Privacy Policy for Your SaaS App in 2026"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted mb-12","children":"Published March 16, 2026 · 14 min read"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-custom space-y-6 text-base text-muted leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"Every SaaS application needs a privacy policy. It is not optional. GDPR requires one if you have any EU users. The CCPA requires one if you have California users. And practically every app store, payment processor, and enterprise buyer will ask for one before doing business with you."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Yet most SaaS founders treat privacy policies as an afterthought — copying a template from another website, running it through ChatGPT, or ignoring it until a customer asks. The result is a document that either says nothing useful or makes promises the application does not keep. Both outcomes create legal liability."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"This guide walks you through writing a privacy policy for a SaaS application from scratch. It covers what the law actually requires, what your users expect, and how to create a document that accurately reflects your application's data practices. Whether you are pre-launch or updating an existing policy, you will find practical, actionable guidance here."}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"Why your SaaS privacy policy matters more than you think"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A privacy policy is not just a legal document. It is a trust signal. Enterprise buyers review it during procurement. Privacy- conscious users read it before signing up. Regulators use it as the first evidence in enforcement actions. And increasingly, AI governance frameworks reference privacy policies as baseline compliance documentation."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"In 2026, the stakes are higher than ever. GDPR enforcement has produced over 4.5 billion EUR in fines across more than 2,000 cases. The CCPA (now CPRA) has an active enforcement division. New state privacy laws in Texas, Oregon, Montana, and others took effect in 2024 and 2025. The EU AI Act adds transparency requirements for AI-powered applications. Your privacy policy needs to address all of these."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A well-written SaaS privacy policy also reduces support burden. When users can find clear answers about data handling, they file fewer tickets. When enterprise buyers can quickly verify your data practices, sales cycles shorten. It is a business advantage disguised as a legal requirement."}],"$L2","$L3","$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18","$L19","$L1a","$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f","$L20","$L21","$L22","$L23","$L24","$L25","$L26","$L27","$L28","$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c","$L2d","$L2e","$L2f","$L30","$L31","$L32","$L33","$L34","$L35","$L36","$L37","$L38","$L39","$L3a","$L3b","$L3c"]}],"$L3d","$L3e"]}]}]],null,"$L3f"]}],"loading":null,"isPartial":false}
2:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"Legal requirements: what the law says you must include"}]
3:["$","p",null,{"children":"Different jurisdictions have different requirements, but most privacy laws converge on the same core disclosures. Here is what you must include to comply with the major frameworks:"}]
4:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"GDPR requirements (EU/EEA users)"}]
5:["$","p",null,{"children":"The General Data Protection Regulation requires your privacy policy to disclose:"}]
6:["$","ul",null,{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Identity and contact details"}]," of the data controller (your company) and your Data Protection Officer if you have one."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Categories of personal data"}]," you collect, with specificity. \"We collect personal information\" is not sufficient. List the actual data: email addresses, IP addresses, usage analytics, payment information, and so on."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Legal basis for processing"}]," each category of data. Under GDPR, you must identify whether you process data based on consent, contractual necessity, legitimate interest, or legal obligation."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Data retention periods"}]," for each category, or the criteria used to determine retention."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Third parties"}]," with whom you share data, including sub-processors, analytics providers, and payment processors."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"International data transfers"}]," and the safeguards in place (Standard Contractual Clauses, adequacy decisions, etc.)."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"User rights"}]," including access, rectification, erasure, portability, restriction, and the right to object."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Right to lodge a complaint"}]," with a supervisory authority."]}]]}]
7:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"CCPA/CPRA requirements (California users)"}]
8:["$","p",null,{"children":"The California Consumer Privacy Act, as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act, requires:"}]
9:["$","ul",null,{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Categories of personal information"}]," collected in the preceding 12 months."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Sources"}]," of that information (directly from users, from third parties, automatically collected)."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Business purposes"}]," for collection and use."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Categories of third parties"}]," with whom you share information."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Whether you sell or share personal information"}],", and if so, a \"Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information\" link."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Consumer rights"}]," including the right to know, delete, correct, and opt out."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Financial incentives"}]," tied to data collection, if any."]}]]}]
a:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Other US state privacy laws"}]
b:["$","p",null,{"children":"As of 2026, over 15 US states have comprehensive privacy laws in effect. While each has nuances, they generally require the same core disclosures as CCPA plus specific rights like appeal processes and opt-out preference signals. A well-structured GDPR and CCPA compliant privacy policy will cover most state requirements, but you should verify against each state where you have significant user populations."}]
c:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"SaaS-specific considerations most templates miss"}]
d:["$","p",null,{"children":"Generic privacy policy templates are written for generic websites. SaaS applications have unique data practices that require specific disclosures. Here is what most templates miss:"}]
e:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"User-generated content and customer data"}]
f:["$","p",null,{"children":"SaaS applications store customer data — the content your users create and manage within your application. This is fundamentally different from data you collect about users. Your privacy policy must distinguish between data you collect for your own purposes (analytics, billing, support) and data your customers store using your service. For the latter, you are typically a data processor under GDPR, not a data controller, and different obligations apply."}]
10:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Third-party integrations and sub-processors"}]
11:["$","p",null,{"children":"Most SaaS applications integrate with dozens of third-party services: payment processors like Stripe, analytics tools like Mixpanel or PostHog, error tracking like Sentry, email delivery via SendGrid or Resend, cloud hosting on AWS or Vercel, and AI APIs from OpenAI or Anthropic. Each of these is a sub-processor that handles your users' data."}]
12:["$","p",null,{"children":"Your privacy policy must disclose these third parties. GDPR requires you to name them or at minimum categorize them. Best practice is to maintain a sub-processor list that you reference from your privacy policy. This list should include the sub-processor name, purpose, data processed, and location."}]
13:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"AI features and automated decision-making"}]
14:["$","p",null,{"children":"If your SaaS uses AI — and most do in 2026 — your privacy policy must address it. GDPR Article 22 gives users the right not to be subject to decisions based solely on automated processing. The EU AI Act adds transparency requirements for AI systems. Your privacy policy should disclose what AI features your application includes, what data they process, whether they make or influence decisions, and how users can opt out or request human review."}]
15:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Multi-tenant data isolation"}]
16:["$","p",null,{"children":"SaaS applications are multi-tenant by nature. Your privacy policy should reassure users that their data is logically isolated from other customers. While you do not need to describe your technical architecture, stating that customer data is isolated and not accessible to other customers builds trust and addresses a common concern in enterprise procurement."}]
17:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"Step-by-step: writing your SaaS privacy policy"}]
18:["$","p",null,{"children":"Here is a practical process for creating a privacy policy that is both legally compliant and genuinely useful."}]
19:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Step 1: Audit your actual data practices"}]
1a:["$","p",null,{"children":"Before writing anything, you need to know what your application actually does with data. This is where most privacy policies go wrong — they are written based on assumptions rather than facts. Run Codepliant against your codebase to generate an accurate inventory of data collection, third-party integrations, and AI usage:"}]
1b:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-code-bg text-code-fg px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-mono text-sm","children":"npx codepliant go"}]
1c:["$","p",null,{"children":"Codepliant scans your package.json, source code imports, environment variables, and configuration files to detect services like Stripe, Google Analytics, Sentry, OpenAI, and dozens more. The output tells you exactly what data your application collects and which third parties it shares data with."}]
1d:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Step 2: Map data flows"}]
1e:["$","p",null,{"children":"For each data category, document where data comes from (user input, automatic collection, third parties), where it is stored (your database, third-party services, CDNs), who can access it (your team, sub-processors, AI providers), and how long it is retained."}]
1f:["$","p",null,{"children":"This mapping exercise reveals disclosures you might otherwise miss. For example, if you use Sentry for error tracking, stack traces may contain user data. If you use an AI API, user inputs may be sent to the AI provider's servers. These data flows must be disclosed."}]
20:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Step 3: Structure the document"}]
21:["$","p",null,{"children":"A well-structured SaaS privacy policy should include these sections:"}]
22:["$","ol",null,{"className":"list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 ml-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Introduction"}]," — Who you are, what the policy covers, effective date."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Information we collect"}]," — Broken down by category: account data, usage data, payment data, customer content, cookies and tracking."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"How we use your information"}]," — Specific purposes tied to specific data categories."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Legal basis for processing"}]," — Required for GDPR compliance."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"How we share your information"}]," — Sub-processors, legal requirements, business transfers."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"International data transfers"}]," — Safeguards for cross-border data flows."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Data retention"}]," — How long you keep each category."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Your rights"}]," — GDPR rights, CCPA rights, how to exercise them."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"AI and automated processing"}]," — AI features, data sent to AI providers, opt-out options."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Security"}]," — Overview of security measures."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Children's privacy"}]," — Age restrictions and COPPA compliance."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Changes to this policy"}]," — How you notify users of updates."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Contact information"}]," — How to reach you with privacy questions."]}]]}]
23:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Step 4: Write in plain language"}]
24:["$","p",null,{"children":"GDPR explicitly requires that privacy policies be written in \"clear and plain language.\" This means avoiding legal jargon, using short sentences, and structuring information so users can find what they need quickly. Write at an eighth-grade reading level. Use headings and bullet points. Define technical terms when you must use them."}]
25:["$","p",null,{"children":"Bad: \"We may process certain categories of personal data insofar as such processing is necessary for the legitimate interests pursued by the controller or by a third party.\""}]
26:["$","p",null,{"children":"Good: \"We use your email address to send you account notifications and product updates. You can opt out of product updates at any time from your account settings.\""}]
27:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Step 5: Keep it accurate and up to date"}]
28:["$","p",null,{"children":"A privacy policy is only as good as its accuracy. Every time you add a new integration, enable a new analytics tool, or ship an AI feature, your privacy policy may need updating. This is why Codepliant is designed to run in CI/CD pipelines — it regenerates compliance documentation on every deployment, so your privacy policy stays in sync with your actual data practices."}]
29:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"Common privacy policy mistakes SaaS companies make"}]
2a:["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div","Copying a competitor's privacy policy",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1","children":"Copying a competitor's privacy policy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"Their data practices are different from yours. A copied policy will either under-disclose (creating legal risk) or over-disclose (undermining trust by claiming you collect data you do not)."}]]}],["$","div","Using vague language to cover everything",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1","children":"Using vague language to cover everything"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"Phrases like 'we may collect various types of information' violate GDPR's specificity requirements. Regulators have fined companies for vague privacy policies."}]]}],["$","div","Forgetting third-party services",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1","children":"Forgetting third-party services"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"If you use Stripe, Google Analytics, Sentry, or any external API, you are sharing user data with those services. This must be disclosed."}]]}],["$","div","Not disclosing AI data processing",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1","children":"Not disclosing AI data processing"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"If user data is sent to OpenAI or Anthropic for processing, this is a data transfer to a third party. GDPR and the EU AI Act require transparency about AI processing."}]]}],["$","div","Setting it and forgetting it",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1","children":"Setting it and forgetting it"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"Your data practices change every time you ship a feature. A privacy policy written at launch is almost certainly inaccurate six months later."}]]}],["$","div","No retention periods",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl p-5","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1","children":"No retention periods"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm text-muted","children":"GDPR requires specific retention periods or criteria. 'We retain your data for as long as necessary' is not compliant."}]]}]]}]
2b:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"SaaS privacy policy template: what to include in each section"}]
2c:["$","p",null,{"children":"While every SaaS application is different, here is a template outline with guidance on what to include in each section. This is not a copy-paste template — it is a framework you should adapt to your actual data practices."}]
2d:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"Information we collect"}]
2e:["$","p",null,{"children":"Break this into clear sub-categories. For a typical SaaS application, these include:"}]
2f:["$","ul",null,{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Account information:"}]," Name, email address, company name, job title. Collected during signup and profile setup."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Payment information:"}]," Credit card details, billing address. Typically processed by Stripe or a similar payment processor — clarify that you do not store raw card numbers."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Usage data:"}]," Pages viewed, features used, session duration, click patterns. Collected via analytics tools."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Device and technical data:"}]," IP address, browser type, operating system, device identifiers. Collected automatically."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Customer content:"}]," Data your users create, upload, or store within your application. Clarify your role as data processor for this content."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Communications:"}]," Support tickets, emails, chat messages. Retained for support quality and dispute resolution."]}]]}]
30:["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-2","children":"How we use your information"}]
31:["$","p",null,{"children":"Tie each use to a specific purpose and, for GDPR, a legal basis:"}]
32:["$","ul",null,{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Providing the service:"}]," Account information and customer content are processed to deliver the service you signed up for. Legal basis: contractual necessity."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Billing:"}]," Payment information is processed to charge for subscriptions. Legal basis: contractual necessity."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Analytics and improvement:"}]," Usage data helps us understand how features are used and prioritize improvements. Legal basis: legitimate interest."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Support:"}]," Communications are used to resolve your issues. Legal basis: contractual necessity."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Security:"}]," Technical data is used for fraud prevention and security monitoring. Legal basis: legitimate interest."]}]]}]
33:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"Generate your privacy policy from your codebase"}]
34:["$","p",null,{"children":"Writing a privacy policy manually is time-consuming and error- prone. You have to audit your codebase, identify every integration, map data flows, and then translate all of that into clear legal language. And you have to repeat this process every time your application changes."}]
35:["$","p",null,{"children":"Codepliant automates this entire process. It scans your source code, detects third-party services and data collection patterns, and generates a privacy policy that accurately reflects your application's data practices. Because it reads your actual code, the output is specific to your application — not a generic template."}]
36:["$","p",null,{"children":"To generate a privacy policy for your SaaS application:"}]
37:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-code-bg text-code-fg px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-mono text-sm","children":"npx codepliant go"}]
38:["$","p",null,{"children":"Codepliant produces a markdown privacy policy alongside terms of service, cookie policy, and AI disclosure documentation. Run it in your CI/CD pipeline to keep your compliance documents synchronized with your code."}]
39:["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground pt-4","children":"Keeping your privacy policy current"}]
3a:["$","p",null,{"children":"A privacy policy is a living document. Here are the events that should trigger a review and potential update:"}]
3b:["$","ul",null,{"className":"list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":"Adding a new third-party integration or sub-processor"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Shipping an AI feature or changing AI providers"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Expanding to new markets or jurisdictions"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Changing data retention practices"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Adding new data collection points (forms, tracking, etc.)"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Changes to applicable privacy laws"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Acquisitions, mergers, or other corporate changes"}]]}]
3c:["$","p",null,{"children":"When you update your privacy policy, notify existing users. GDPR does not prescribe a specific notification method, but best practice is an in-app banner or email notification with a summary of changes and a link to the updated policy."}]
3d:["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-surface rounded-2xl p-8 text-center mt-16 mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold mb-3","children":"Generate your SaaS privacy policy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted text-sm mb-6","children":"Scan your codebase to generate a privacy policy based on your actual data practices. Free, open source, no account required."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-code-bg text-code-fg px-6 py-3 rounded-xl font-mono text-sm inline-block","children":"npx codepliant go"}]]}]
3e:["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6","children":"Related resources"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-3","children":[["$","a","/privacy-policy-generator",{"href":"/privacy-policy-generator","className":"block bg-surface rounded-xl p-4 hover:ring-1 hover:ring-border-strong transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1 text-sm","children":"Privacy Policy Generator"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-muted","children":"Generate a privacy policy from your codebase in seconds."}]]}],["$","a","/blog/gdpr-for-developers",{"href":"/blog/gdpr-for-developers","className":"block bg-surface rounded-xl p-4 hover:ring-1 hover:ring-border-strong transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1 text-sm","children":"GDPR Compliance for Developers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-muted","children":"Practical GDPR guide for engineering teams building SaaS products."}]]}],["$","a","/gdpr-compliance",{"href":"/gdpr-compliance","className":"block bg-surface rounded-xl p-4 hover:ring-1 hover:ring-border-strong transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1 text-sm","children":"GDPR Compliance Hub"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-muted","children":"Everything you need to know about GDPR compliance for your application."}]]}],["$","a","/data-privacy",{"href":"/data-privacy","className":"block bg-surface rounded-xl p-4 hover:ring-1 hover:ring-border-strong transition-shadow","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-semibold mb-1 text-sm","children":"Data Privacy Compliance Hub"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-muted","children":"Overview of all compliance frameworks Codepliant supports."}]]}]]}]]}]
